---
description: API route conventions for src/app/api
globs: src/app/api/**
alwaysApply: false
---

# API routes

- Keep route handlers thin
- Delegate to module services
- Use helpers from `src/lib/server/api.ts` such as `withSwitchRequestContext`
- Use `src/lib/server/request-context.ts` for auth and request boundaries
- Do not put business rules directly in route files

# UI routes

- Page components fetch through the API layer or existing server bridges
- Do not duplicate module logic in `src/app/**/page.tsx`
